{
  "text": "We describe the decomposition algorithm using the four-node optical network modeled by the queueing network shown in Figure 2 Beginning with subsystem 1, each subsystem is analyzed in sequence. Within a subsystem, each node is analyzed iteratively using the single-node decomposition method assuming link independence. For subsystem 1, the only traffic arriving to the node is Poisson traffic. The node is analyzed using (7), (8) and demands d r . The nodes are analyzed using (7), [CITATION_1] , and (9) assuming 2R classes. The algorithm then shifts to node 2 on wavelength 2. ",
